Wolverhampton Wanderers' Portuguese head coach Nuno Espirito Santo gestures on the touchline. AFP/Peter Powell LONDON - Nuno Espirito Santo has been charged by the Football Association. The Wolves coach has been charged with breaching FA rules for his comments about referee Lee Mason. He accused Mason of lacking the qualities to be a referee at the top level. Santo told Mason after the Wolves 2-1 loss to Burnley that he would not like to see him refereeing his team again. He now has until 5 January to respond to the FA charge of bringing the game into disrepute.